articles.title: Nasa spacecraft successfully 'pings' Chandrayaan-3 Vikram lander on Moon - Business Standard
articles.description: Laser instrument onboard a NASA spacecraft orbiting the Moon has successfully pinged the Vikram lander of India's Chandrayaan-3 mission, the US space agency said.
articles.content:
The lander was 100 kilometers away from LRO, near Manzinus crater in the Moon's south pole region, when LRO transmitted laser pulses toward it on December 12 last year
